HEADWORD: Thoroughgoing
<hw>Thor"ough*go`ing</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Going through, or to the end or bottom; very thorough;
complete.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Going all lengths; extreme; thoroughplaced; -- less
common in this sense.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Thorough-lighted</ent>⟦br⟧
